news.title: Over 300 structures razed, restaurants sealed in demolition drive in Gurugram
news.para: The demolition covered a Stilt +4 building on Plot 33 and two restaurants. Additionally, two green areas were cleared of encroachments.

news.title: Land survey for Coimbatore metro work begins on March 5
news.para: The land plan survey is set to commence from Wednesday for 35 kilometres in total - 20.4km for corridor I on Avinashi Road and 14.4km for corridor II on Sathyamangalam Road.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to hold doorstep drive to fix property ID errors
news.para: The decision was made at a monthly review meeting on Monday, chaired by MCG commissioner Ashok Kumar Garg, who said, "Teams should be formed to visit households to ensure that errors in property tax data are corrected swiftly."

news.title: Pune civic body proposes no hike in property tax in budget 2025-26
news.para: Redevelopment of properties in the old city areas, projects in the new areas and a share of revenue from PMRDA construction approvals are expected to boost revenue from building permissions.

news.title: Diversion tax unpaid, farmhouse & office of coloniser sealed by Indore administration
news.para: The officials sealed the office of a coloniser, Vidyut Mittal, situated in Mhowgaon, for failing to clear a land diversion tax of around Rs 18 lakh due on his Super City Colony.

news.title: MMRCL plans to monetise land parcels along Mumbai metro 3 corridor
news.para: The land parcels, situated in Byculla, Marol, Mahim and Dharavi, totalling about 12,491 square metres, are located along the Mumbai Metro Line 3 corridor and MMRCL is planning to monetise these through strategic joint ventures, public-private partnerships (PPP) or outright sales, according to people familiar with the matter.

news.title: SC upholds eviction for Bharat Nagar slum redevelopment in Bandra East
news.para: The SC held that it was a 'censused slum' and said such slums are already included in the definition of slums for redevelopment; thus, no separate notification is required under the Slum Act.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 2,338 properties of tax defaulters
news.para: In the southwest zone of the city, 466 properties were sealed, resulting in a recovery of Rs 32.70 lakh in a single day.

news.title: MahaRERA denies relief to Ekta Tripolis buyers as complaint filed after possession offer
news.para: ​The regulatory authority stated that the claim of interest for delay or compensation for delay in possession under section 18 of the RERA can only be invoked when the promoter fails to complete the project or is unable to give possession as per the date specified in the agreement.

news.title: SC proposes a CBI probe into builders-banks nexus
news.para: The court was hearing petitions filed by thousands of homebuyers, who had booked flats under subvention plans in various housing projects in NCR, alleging that they are being forced by banks to pay EMI even when they were yet to get possession of their flats because of inordinate delay by developers.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body cancels Motera plot allotment as builder defaults on deposit
news.para: The plot on Motera's TP Scheme No. 21, was purchased by Pramukh Imaging Center for Rs 15.11 crore at a rate of Rs 1.57 lakh per sq m. The standing committee approved the sale proposal on Oct 30, 2024.

news.title: FIR lodged against Ansal Group after Uttar Pradesh CM's instructions
news.para: ​The FIR was registered a day after Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath instructed officials to take strict action in the matter and safeguard homebuyers' interest.

news.title: IBC moratorium does not shield individuals from penalties under consumer law: SC
news.para: It was argued by Saranga Anilkumar Aggarwal that he was facing insolvency proceedings before the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) under the IBC and hence there should be a stay on the execution of an NCDRC (National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission) order.

news.title: Functioning of RERA disappointing, says SC
news.para: He pointed to the "domino effect" engulfing the real estate sector and said if one project of a builder fails, then his other projects also collapse and the courts cannot adjudicate matters related to the failed project.

news.title: Embassy REIT invests Rs 100 crore to develop Bengaluru's Kadubeesanahalli metro station
news.para: The station will be named as Embassy TechVillage Kadubeesanahalli Metro Station for a period of 30 years from its commercial operation date.

news.title: Sumadhura Group forays into plotted development
news.para: Panorama is spread over 100 acres of land with its first phase spread across a 50-acres land and comprises 539 plots ranging between 1,200 sq ft to 7,000 sq ft.

news.title: Shakti Kapoor sells apartment in Mumbai's Juhu for Rs 6.11 crore
news.para: Shakti Kapoor's apartment has a built-up area of 81.84 sq meters (881 sq ft). The transaction incurred a stamp duty payment of Rs 36.66 lakh.

news.title: Cement prices fall 7% in Apr-Jan FY25: Report
news.para: It further said the volume ramp-up from some of the acquired capacities that were operating sub-optimally earlier would keep the prices under pressure over the near term.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat invests Rs 3,520 crore to boost cement capacity to 55.5 million tonnes
news.para: Dalmia acknowledged that short-term headwinds existed in the form of a price war that was driving down margins of players but believes that doesn't change the long-term view.

news.title: Ambuja Cements gets CCI nod to acquire majority stake in Orient Cement
news.para: "The proposed transaction comprises the acquisition of 46.80 per cent of the issued share capital in the target (Orient Cement) by the acquirer (Ambuja Cements)," CCI said in a release.
